    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to modern prints produced by the carborundum mezzotint process, developed in the 20th century and by which mezzotint-like tone is achieved by roughening the surface of the plate with abrasives. Such prints will have the general quality of a mezzotint but will not show in the lighter areas the straight lines of the rocker's serrated edge.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000016051/Gascoigne, How to Identify Prints (1986)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000096407/Concise Oxford Dictionary of Art Terms [online] (2001-2008)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere a estampas modernas producidas según el proceso de mezzotinta al carborundo. Estas estampas tendrán la calidad general de mezzotinta pero no muestran, en las áreas más luminosas, las líneas rectas del canto aserrado del graneador.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar moderne afdrukken die zijn geproduceerd aan de hand van het carborundum-mezzotintprocedé. Dergelijke afdrukken hebben de algemene eigenschappen van een mezzotint, maar vertonen in de lichtere gebieden niet de rechte lijnen van de zaagvormige randen van de wiegijzers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以碳化矽美柔汀版畫製作程序加以創作的現代版畫，發展自西元二十世紀間，此技法使用研磨料摩擦銅版表面以達到美柔汀版畫的效果。這類版畫多具有美柔汀版畫的整體效果，但在明亮處不會見到搖移器鋸齒狀邊緣所製造出的直線線條。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
